OL,7,F"There is a growing body of evidence
OL,8,Fthat this is having a harmful impact
OL,9,Fparticularly on women and girls hence
OL,10,FBaroness Bertin's review, commissioned
OL,11,Fby the government, to see how this
OL,12,Fcontent should be regulated more
OL,13,Feffectively in the future."
OL,15,FThe government has in recent years
OL,16,Fsought to regulate the sector. By July
OL,17,F2025, all websites hosting
OL,18,Fpornographic material must introduce
OL,19,Fage verification under measures
OL,20,Fannounced by Ofcom.
